</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/umakaniikaika.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Makani Ikaika</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast Prince</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#871F78>(5/31/02 9:27:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1725.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: rambling  - Beastlord vs a rouge, a bard, and a monk</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> For a break, I am thinking of 3 classes and trying to settle on one or the other. When I list pro's and con's, I am basing them on what I have read on Casters realm and class related sights.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
There is your first mistake. Beleiving anything on castersrealm is a bad habit. They are a good source for GENERAL information, but their class sections just plain suck IMO. And they are full of misinformation and just outright wrong information.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Bard - <br>
Pros - liked in group, no mana, can travel well, can stand up and melee in situations. <br>
Con - can't solo, unable to find a decent bard msg board, my arms already are on the verge of carpal tunnel.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Bards do have mana, but it's not used all that much except for in the 39-55 range. During this time we have a charm that uses 20 mana. Doesn't sound like much till you chain charm and realize that we don't get affected by clarity or any other mana giving abilities (Including Mod Rods). There's also some AE song too, but that one sucks for the 800 mana it blows =p<br>
<br>
You say that a Bard can't solo, and I tell you that you have never met a Bard. I can solo very well at 60, in or out of dungeons. I do it all the time.<br>
<br>
Here is the two definitive Bard boards. I personally prefer the first for discussion.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.attcanada.net/~reaper/">www.attcanada.net/~reaper/</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
and<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqdiva.com">www.eqdiva.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I've started a cleric and a wizard, but seems that I am stuck on being a character type that gets in and is constantly busy and mixing things up. <br>
<br>
Any thoughts, comments, advise? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
A good Bard is a rare find. When you find one you will know it. They will pull off things you would have evacced from ages ago. They will make a good group a killing machine. They will completely remove downtime, and in a broken group they will really shine as they take over a role that is missing.<br>
<br>
However, a bad Bard is something to run away from at your top speed and hope it doesn't follow.<br>
<br>
If you play a Bard, take the time to get to know your songs. Even songs that seem stupid are sometimes the best thing you can play in a certain situation. <p><HR>
