</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ukambok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><CENTER>Beast Lord</CENTER></span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#871F78>(5/31/02 11:34:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1725.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: rambling  - Beastlord vs a rouge, a bard, and a monk</span><hr size=1> With my lvl-36 bard, I can solo NON-STOP for hours.<br>
<br>
I have 5 different ways I can solo as  a bard.<br>
<br>
1.)Run around and kite the mob, using our DD and dot songs.<br>
<br>
2.) Charm kite, charm a mob and sick it on another mob. Have charmed mob kill mob, or switch charms if your main guy is losing.<br>
<br>
3.) Swarm kitting, This works great on mobs that are social. IE.. Pull a snow cugar and let it get 4-6 more snow cougars... Charm one and send it on the whole pack. Once your charm wears off, the mob is practically dead. Twist a dot and a couple DD songs and its dead.<br>
<br>
4.) Fear kite the mobs with snare/fear and melee it to death.<br>
<br>
5.) Stand there and sing both slow songs and just tank the mob.<br>
<br>
<br>
Numbers 2, 3, and 4 are the best for expies. Swarm kitting is INSANE exp. I can gain around one or two blue bubbles every 5-6 mins.<br>
<br>
<br>
The bard class is VERY amazing if you can play them well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/umemak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>memak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Primal Ooze</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#871F78>(5/31/02 11:54:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1725.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: rambling  - Beastlord vs a rouge, a bard, and a monk</span><hr size=1> I've played most every class and bard is my current and longest lasting main.<br>
<br>
<b>Bards solo very well!</b><br>
If nothing else, bards are masters of downtime.  They solo very well with charm, chants, or even melee.  They are not uber damage dealers, but their huge versitality more than makes up for it.  However, they are not an easy class to master, and you will stay busy twisting songs almost all the time.  Don't play bard if your hands can't take the real life beating.<br>
<br>
<b>Monks solo very well!</b><br>
Not as well as bards at higher levels and much better at lower levels with a fungi tunic.  Monks level very fast with twink equipment.  If you like pulling, monks are fun.  They are not always the best pullers, but FD gives a huge margin for error.  Even so, I'd stick with your 49 SK if you want to go the FD puller route.  SK's, IMHO, are simply superior pullers to monks.<br>
<br>
<b>Rogues are damage!</b><br>
They suck without a group, but with a tank they can deal massive damage and level pretty fast.  Still, I got tired of my rogue pretty fast.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps. <p><P>
